items.text:
We‚Äôre looking for **live performers **to portray a modern family for an **immersive, non-speaking activation** at Waterloo Station. This is a **non-speaking role**, focused on naturalistic, observational performance. Scenes will include moments such as preparing dinner together, plating food, sitting down and sharing an unhurried family meal.

Real families with performance experience welcome! 

Looking to recruit for the following:

**Roles:**

‚Ä¢ 4√ó Adults (playing 30‚Äì45)

‚Ä¢ 4√ó Youth Actors (playing 8‚Äì15, older considered. (Child Performance Licence required (support provided)

‚Ä¢ Well-trained family dog (optional)

**Dates:**

‚Ä¢ 14 Jan ‚Äì Rehearsal Date - Paid

‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì22 Jan ‚Äì Live performance (TBC on which families work which dates)

**Times (20‚Äì22 Jan):**

3.30pm call | 5‚Äì6pm live | 6-6-30pm change

**Rate:** ¬£250 per shift (updated)

**Note:** Filmed for social media. 

**Apply:** [recruit@weareplay.co.uk](mailto:recruit@weareplay.co.uk)

Please include your showreel/profile (if you have one), headshot & full body photo, a 30-sec intro video on why you would fit the part, relevant experience + availability and confirmation you are self-employed. 

Looking at applications on Friday 26th December so please get your applications in. 

Thanks!

Hello, I'm Martine and something to know about me is. I‚Äôm based in Sandbach and currently looking for new opportunities as a model.
I describe myself as warm, friendly and someone who gives 100% to everything I do.

I take pride in being professional, approachable and easy to connect with, qualities I believe help me to relate to people of all ages and backgrounds.

I have always had a strong sense of style and enjoy expressing that through my work, whether it is in front of a camera or working with a team on a project.

I love the creative side of modeling and working with photographers, stylists and other artists to tell a story or capture the perfect image for a brand.

items.text: My son is wanting to become an actor, he is a member of The Pauline Quirk academy and has had his debut on the West end. What advice can you give to him to help progress, I am helping him in this journey and want to seek out jobs for him.

topComments.text:
Tell to be realistic. Enjoy the journey.
Don‚Äôt make stardom and fane his goal.
It‚Äôs far better to be a working actor, that works continuously. But enjoy the journey. Be prepared to make sacrifices, do jobs that no one wants and thar normally he never consider, bills stlll have to be paid, equity, Spotlight, headshots. But enjoy the journey. Keep the passion, keep the faith and don‚Äôt quit before the miracle.
It is a hard game, some get lucky, some don‚Äôt but as long as you enjoy the journey . And when things go right enjoy the moment, it‚Äôs the greatest feeling and better than any drug.
But enjoy the journey.  I am 63. Been in the business for along time and I still enjoy the journey.
Good luck

The Ghost That Could- Casting Call/Updates

Grateful the project was recently awarded the: @fromtheheartproductions ‚ÄòHot Film In The Making Roy W. Dean Grant FALL 2025‚Äô laurel

Excited to be moving into the test shoots stage of production in coming months(Jan-April). I went ahead and emailed some self tape request to those who expressed serious interest via email-

To anyone who responded before who is still interested in being part of the team/actor email: mattiemacaya@gmail.com with a resume and area of skill, attach resume

For self tapes please follow below instructions: 

For this stage, we would love to see a short, silent self-tape that gives us a sense of your emotional range and presence. No monologue is needed. 

Please submit this by NO LATER then end of dayJanuary 17 2026. For anyone interested in production assisting/marketing/makeup/etc email NO LATER then end of day January 20 2026.

What to include:

* Film either inside or outside ‚Äî whatever feels most comfortable and natural to you
* Keep the framing horizontal
* A simple moment where you move through an emotion or emotional shift (this can be very subtle)30seconds to 1 minute. 
* Please include a brief slate at the end with your name

After the slate, please answer the following two questions on camera (casually ‚Äî no need to overthink):

1. When do you feel most like yourself?
2. What‚Äôs something you notice about people that others often miss?

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Shoot Details: 

Test Shoot for Film Short

Non-union

Shoot Dates: TBD January - April 2026

Rate of Pay: Food/Beverage provided

Location: Denver, CO and surrounding locations

Side note from the üëª : if you‚Äôre submitting note the team will not respond to direct PMs on here nor will anyone chase you down for follow up if you are selected- that is ON YOU. Meet the self tape/application deadline if you‚Äòre serious and can commit, there can only be ONE ghost on this project everyone else will have to haunt elsewhere.

Thank you all for continued interest and support! Let‚Äôs collaborate on some magical storytelling in the new year and get this on 2026-2027 Festival Circuit.

Setgefl√ºster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl√ºster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur √ºber Drehtage, Abl√§ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern √ºber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. Denn auch wenn jemand vor der Kamera souver√§n wirkt, bedeutet das nicht, dass innen alles leicht ist. 

Der Einstieg f√ºhlt sich erst nach lockerer Pause an, kurze Begr√º√üung, ein bisschen Set-Alltag, dieses Gef√ºhl von, wir reden einfach. Und dann kippt es in eine Situation, die viele kennen, aber kaum jemand anspricht: Narben werden sichtbar. 

Genau hier passiert etwas Wichtiges: Wir zeigen, wie man N√§he nicht durch Schweigen baut, sondern durch Haltung. Denn Respekt ist nicht, so zu tun als w√§re nichts da. Respekt ist, den Menschen zu sehen und die richtige Form zu finden. Im Gespr√§ch wird klar, dass es einen Unterschied gibt zwischen Starren und ehrlicher Neugier, zwischen Voyeurismus und Verbindung. 

Dann wird es konkret, weil wir nicht nur √ºber Narben als Symbol sprechen, sondern √ºber Narben als medizinisches Thema. Es f√§llt der Begriff Keloidnarben, dazu hypertrophe Narben, und sogar die Info, dass es unterschiedliche Auspr√§gungen geben kann. 

Was Setgefl√ºster Teil 4 besonders macht, ist die n√§chste Ebene: Intimit√§t und Selbstwert. Wir sprechen dar√ºber, was es bedeutet, wenn man seinen K√∂rper nicht einfach neutral erlebt, sondern als etwas, das bewertet wird. Da geht es um Licht, das man lieber ausmacht. 

Und hier kommt der Br√ºckenschlag zur Schauspielerei: Eine Rolle verlangt Pr√§senz. Pr√§senz bedeutet, Du bist da, mit K√∂rper, Stimme, Blick, Atmung. 

Zu mir, Christian Wei√üe 

Ich bin Christian Wei√üe, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K√∂ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz√§hle Geschichten f√ºr Unternehmen,Organisationen und Pers√∂nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Wie w√ºrdest Du wollen, dass man Dich auf etwas Sichtbares an Deinem K√∂rper anspricht, damit es sich respektvoll anf√ºhlt? 

Gef√§llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke, gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, schreib Deine Sicht in die Kommentare und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f√ºr weitere Impulse.

Ciao, we are LeZgo Agency Agency an **Italian Animation** **& Event** **Agency**.

We are looking for Staff, who want to work next Summer 2026 on Garda Lake in Animation Staff, **with Dutch or German Language.**

**_**

We are looking for :

**-Responsabile Staff ( with demstrable Experience )**

**- Sport**

**- Mini Club**

**- Fitness**

**_**

Lezgo will provide :

**- Food and accommodation ( With bathroom and air conditioning )**

**- A travel budget**

**- A good basic salary**

**( Depends of the Experience but we start from 700 ‚Ç¨ a month Minimun )**

**- A regular Italian Contract**

_

The availability required is:

**- From 1 April, til 4 October (full Season )**

**- From 23 May, til 7 June**

**- From 6 july, til 15 September**

(We also evaluate availability for short periods)

_

Working hours :

**- 2 Hours morning**

**- 2 Hours afternoon**

**- 2 Hours Evening**

**( there ll be no surprise like, tests/rehearsals during the breaks )**

**- 1 Day off a Week**

**_**

By Email : **Lezgo.agency@gmail.com**

Click below, on the post button ( Cristian )

**_**

We are waiting for you!

items.text:
What Casting Directors Are Actually Looking For

Actors often think auditions are about impressing. Casting Directors are actually looking for clarity, professionalism, and trust.
Every audition silently answers three questions:
Can you do the role?
Can you take direction?
Can we work with you?
When you understand that, your auditions change completely.
üîó Read the full guide:
üëâ https://cineconnectstagecraft.org

‚ú® CASTING CALL ‚Äì A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL) ‚ú®

Do you want to be part of something special next summer?

Are you looking for a creative project that helps you grow as a performer, collaborate with other artists, and build your portfolio?

We‚Äôre casting for A Place Not Mine, an original cabaret musical inspired by real-life experiences of the writer, reimagined in a magical world influenced by shows like Wicked and contemporary musical theatre.

A story about belonging, identity, love, and finding your voice.

We are looking for London-based actors / actor-singers who are excited to collaborate and tell meaningful stories together.

üé≠ Roles available:

Riven ¬∑ Seraphine ¬∑ Mirra ¬∑ Selene ¬∑ Aurora ¬∑ Oris ¬∑ Vespera ¬∑ Sylas ¬∑ Rowan

üåø Please note:

The role of Riven includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). We are looking for performers who feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

üìå Project information:

This is an unpaid project, created as a development / showcase production, with the aim of presenting the work in a professional theatre setting.

The project will offer:

‚Ä¢ Professional performance credit

‚Ä¢ Showreel / recorded footage of the final performance

‚Ä¢ A collaborative, supportive rehearsal process

üìÜ Availability:

Rehearsals expected to take place between March/April‚Äì July, with performances planned for July/August. (exact dates TBC).

üì© How to audition:

Please send:

‚Ä¢ CV

‚Ä¢ Showreel or self-tape

‚Ä¢ Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to: üëâ emilvasilev296@gmail.com, just add the name of the character you're applying for. 

(Feel free to reach out with any questions!)

If this feels like a project you‚Äôd enjoy, we‚Äôd truly love to hear from you üíõ

UK ACTORS WANTED

We‚Äôre preparing for our second filming block in February 2026, and TrueLume Films is casting four short films set within The Chaplain universe. These films serve as character backstories, capturing pivotal moments from the past that quietly shape relationships, choices, and the paths these characters go on to follow.

ROLES AVAILABLE:

AARON JAMES
Age Range: Early 20s
Ethnicity: White British
Aaron is a worship musician connected to The Gathering Church who also works in the Police force. He is driven by faith and a personal loss from his past, which motivates his career and actions. The role requires a grounded, sincere presence.

AARON JAMES (AGED 12)
Age Range: 11‚Äì13
Ethnicity: White British
Young Aaron is a bright, adventurous boy. Protective over his
twin sister. The role requires a passionate and strong personality. 

NAOMI JAMES (AGED 12)
Age Range: 11‚Äì13
Ethnicity: White British
Naomi is Aaron‚Äôs younger twin sister, imaginative 
and full of energy. She loves adventure and sharing a close, playful bond with her brother. The role requires curiosity, and a lively presence.

GRAHAM JONES
Age Range: Late 20s
Ethnicity: White British
Graham is a dedicated police sergeant known for his strong sense of duty and leadership. He is a committed husband who takes his responsibilities seriously at work and at home. The role requires a grounded, dependable presence with subtle emotional depth.

EMMA JONES
Age Range: Late 20s
Ethnicity: White British
Emma is a school teacher and the wife of a Graham Jones. She is gentle, loving, and deeply committed to her marriage. Her ongoing struggle with infertility and IVF has taken an emotional toll. The role requires warmth and quiet emotional honesty.

HARRISON DOYLE
Age Range: Early 20s
Ethnicity: White British
Harrison is a young, energetic police officer, fresh out of 
training and eager to prove himself. The role requires charisma, energy, and a natural sense of impulsive optimism.

KASHIF ALI
Age Range: Early 20s
Ethnicity: South Asian / British Pakistani
Kashif is a streetwise, charismatic young man caught between 
loyalty to his family and the pull of gang life. Quick-thinking, 
persuasive, and complex, the role requires intensity and emotional range.

TAYLOR REYNOLDS
Age Range: Early 20s
Ethnicity: White British
Taylor is a calm, charming member of a local gang who stays under the radar while navigating street life. Observant and adaptable, he talks his way through situations and avoids confrontation. The role requires subtle charisma and quiet confidence.

SERENA CLARKE (AGED 13)
Age Range: 12‚Äì14
Ethnicity: Black British/ Caribbean
Serena is a bright, curious, and empathetic young girl with a playful, joyful energy. Grounded in her faith, she is warm, approachable, and thoughtful. The role requires natural charm, sincerity, and youthful optimism.

EZRA HUGHES (AGED 15)
Age Range: 14‚Äì16
Ethnicity: Mixed British- Black Caribbean
Ezra is a sharp, observant teenager with a quiet intensity. Thoughtful and curious, he navigates adolescence with a mix of skepticism and faith. The role requires a grounded, natural performance with subtle emotional depth.

ARMY INSTRUCTOR
Age Range: 35‚Äì50
Ethnicity: White British Male 
A hardened, no-nonsense drill sergeant who transforms cadets 
into disciplined soldiers. Authoritative, intense, and unyielding, therole requires a commanding presence and the ability to portray strict discipline and authority.

Spotlight actors welcome, but we‚Äôre also open to discovering new talent.

Submit headshot, CV, and reel to: casting@truelumefilms.com

üìçFilming in Newport, South Wales, UK

üé¨ This is a professional production.  All roles are PAID

‚úùÔ∏è Faith-aligned performers encouraged to apply.

American, male, 37‚Äì45 years old, native english speaker, american accent. Professional actor, not a model.

Fee: 120,000 THB (~$3800). An advance payment will be provided.

Travel to Phuket is paid separately if the actor is not based there.

No comment, no DM please. 

Send your photo card and some videos to: art.rin.august@gmail.com

Looking for an actor for a cryptocurrency video project.

Duration: 30 minutes.

2 shooting days.

Location: Phuket, Thailand.

Tentative dates: mid-January

Actor in their own wardrobe.

The video will be used on the company‚Äôs website.

The video cannot be added to the actor‚Äôs portfolio.

To participate in the casting, you will need to record a self-tape reading part of the text.

Thank you all and good luck.

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm a Liverpool-based actor and headshot photographer, shooting from a studio in Whiston / Prescot. I specialise in relaxed, casting-friendly headshots that feel natural and true to you ‚Äî no forced ‚Äúlooks‚Äù or rushed sessions.

With January usually being a quieter month for auditions, I know a lot of us use this time to refresh Spotlight, CVs and materials ready for when things pick up again.

If anyone‚Äôs thinking about updating headshots, check out my portfolio:

üëâ www.fitzyphotography.co.uk

Happy to answer any questions ‚Äî and best of luck to everyone going into the new year üé¨

‚ú® **CASTING CALL ‚Äì A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL)**

We‚Äôre still looking to cast the following roles for our original cabaret musical **A Place Not Mine**, set in the world of **Novattera University**.

üé≠ **Roles still available:**

**RIVEN** ‚Äì emotionally complex, introspective, with strong inner conflict
**SERAPHINE** ‚Äì confident, admired, ambitious, with a soft side beneath
**MIRRA** ‚Äì brave, outspoken, a natural leader who refuses to stay silent
**AURORA** ‚Äì warm, playful, brings light and humour into heavy moments
**SELENE** ‚Äì sharp, witty, loyal, not afraid to speak her mind
**ORIS** ‚Äì kind, quirky, emotionally open, using humour to cope
**ROWAN** ‚Äì observant, sarcastic, awkward in the best way
**ELARA** ‚Äì intelligent, anxious, loyal, quietly funny
**SYLAS** ‚Äì authoritative, controlled, psychologically intense (wicked teacher role)

We‚Äôre looking for **London-based actors / actor-singers** who enjoy character-driven storytelling and working collaboratively on original material.

üåø *Please note:*
The role of **Riven** includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). Performers should feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

üì© **To audition:**
Please send:
‚Ä¢ CV
‚Ä¢ Showreel or self-tape
‚Ä¢ Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to üëâ **emilvasilev296@gmail.com**** or DM **

If any of these roles resonate with you, we‚Äôd love to hear from you ‚ú®
Feel free to message us with any questions.

Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver√§ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh√∂rt, Schauspiel nur √ºber Technik, Wissen und ‚Äûrichtig machen‚Äú zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet ‚Äì mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f√ºr Pr√§senz statt Performance. Wir haben w√∂chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie ‚Äûfertig‚Äú waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr√§senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment ‚Äì in 7 Buchstaben:

E ‚Äì Erleben

S ‚Äì Selbst

S ‚Äì Seele

E ‚Äì Emotion

N ‚Äì N√§he

Z ‚Äì Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

Wenn du den Link m√∂chtest, kommentiere **ESSENZ**.

üé≠casting call üé≠
Paid acting role, payment for performance date itself only. Are you interested in playing the role of fae royalty? Could you be the new ruler of the meadow kingdom? üëëOne of the actors has had to drop out last minute, and so they are looking for a strong improv performer to join the team. 

We appreciate enthusiasm for fantasy, comedy and fun characterisations. You would be giving quests out to ball goers and so the ability to stay in character is important. As there is a lot of improvisation it would be awesome to see what you bring to the role (the character can be tweaked depending on what you bring to the table).

First Sunday of 2026. üé¨

Before the emails.
Before the auditions.
Before the noise starts again, pause here.

Whether you‚Äôre brand new to acting
or you‚Äôve been doing this long enough to know it‚Äôs a marathon, not a sprint, 
today is about intention.
Let‚Äôs set real goals. Not fantasy ones.

Beginners, ask yourself...

‚Ä¢ What skill will I work on this month?
‚Ä¢ What small step will move me forward?
‚Ä¢ What will I stop comparing myself to?

Professionals,  check in honestly...

‚Ä¢ What do I want more of this year?
‚Ä¢ What drains me that I need to let go of?
‚Ä¢ What does success actually look like for me now?

Careers aren‚Äôt built in one audition.
They‚Äôre built in seasons of showing up with purpose.

So don‚Äôt rush 2026.
Shape it.

Write down one clear goal for this month. One habit you‚Äôll commit to.
One thing you‚Äôll do differently.

‚ÄúBeginners set direction. Professionals refine focus. Progress comes from those who choose their next step.‚Äù
‚Äî Casting Calls UK

Drop your one goal for January in the comments üëá
Big or small,  say it out loud.
This is where momentum starts.

Casting Calls UK  üé¨üá¨üáß

# **CASTING CALLS - Student film - Paid**

‚Äî

Hi everyone! We are casting for our final-year film at the University of Hertfordshire. 

Title: Hangman

Genre: Horror, Thriller

Shooting Period: **7th - 22nd** **February 2026** (around 5 days)

Locations: **London, Cambridge,** (/ any other areas nearby)

Pay Rate: **¬£100-200** per day (w/ meal & mileage

allowances according to the **Equity** guideline)

‚Äî

Story:

Ethan, a gambling addict drowning in debt and chased by loan sharks. While his family fall apart, he steals his daughter Emma‚Äôs tuition money for a last-ditch gamble. He ends up losing everything. Broke and haunted by the mysterious Hangman, a manifestation of his guilt and destruction. Ethan breaks into his own home to steal more money, only to be taken toward a deadly showdown on a quiet road.

‚Äî

Lead Roles:

Ethan ** (Male, 35 - 50)**

Bella **(Female, 35 - 50)**

Emma **(Female, 18 - 22)**

(Please check the pictures below for more details.)

‚Äî

Supporting Roles:

THE HANGMAN** (Any Gender & Age 18+)**
* Tall is preferred for an imposing presence.
* Will be hidden under a large black cloak and a mask.

Loan Shark 1 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Should look like someone who spends time on the street, maybe with tattoos or a strong build

Loan Shark 2 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Different from Loan Shark 1 to show contrast.

‚Äî 

If interested, please send your headshots and resumes to sinfulhangman@gmail.com. All levels of experience are welcome!

For more details, please don't hesitate to contact us through email or our Instagram page (hangman.shortfilms)!

**Production Information:**

-Shoot Dates: Feb 21st-22nd.

-Genre:Drama, Thriller

-Non-Union/Volunteer

-Crafty+IMDb credit provided

**Officer Shaw Male 28-50**

A true believer in justice and law enforcement. He doesn‚Äôt believe mentalism is anything more than cheap party tricks, but he finds Chaz and his shtick entertaining, so he allows Chaz to perform for him and explain himself. With every word Chaz says in his defence, Officer Shaw starts to see through Chaz‚Äôs persona and eventually confronts him about the moral, ethical and legal complications his profession entails. The conversation reaches a boiling point when Chaz attempts to read Officer Shaw‚Äôs mind by repeating the last words spoken to Shaw from his missing daughter.

**AUDITION NOTICE** -- LOVE, LOSS AND WHAT I WORE

Authors: Nora Ephron and Delia Ephron (based on the book by Ilene Beckerman)
Director: Olivia Etey
Producer: Janet Ellis
Audition Date/Time: Tuesday, January 6, 7 PM
Location: Peninsula Productions (14600 North Bluff Road, White Rock)

Preparation: Please prepare two short 1-2 minute monologues. One comedic and one dramatic.
Play Summary:

Love, Loss, and What I Wore uses a series of monologues and ensemble vignettes to explore the
female experience through the lens of fashion. By using clothing as a "time capsule," the play
recounts pivotal life moments‚Äîmarriages, heartbreaks, and family dynamics‚Äîall triggered by
memories of specific garments. From the universal struggle of bra shopping to poignant stories of
resilience and grief, the production highlights how a woman‚Äôs wardrobe serves as a roadmap of her
identity and history.

Characters:
The play features a diverse ensemble of 5‚Äì7 women ages 40+. Except for Gingy, all actors portray
multiple characters.

Gingy: The central narrator and anchor of the play. She is wise and self-deprecating,
recounting her life story from childhood through several marriages and milestones.
Ensemble A (The Matriarch/Dramatist): Primarily portrays mother figures and women
navigating deep loss or family traditions.
Ensemble B (The Comedian): Handles high-energy, humorous rants regarding fashion
frustrations, such as the "I Hate My Purse" monologue.
Ensemble C (The Survivor): Focuses on characters navigating life‚Äôs hardships, including stories
of illness, aging, and reclaiming personal power.
Ensemble D (The Ingenue/Rebel): Portrays younger characters dealing with first loves,
wedding dress shopping, and finding their identity through style.

This staged reading will be at Peninsula Studio Theatre from March 5, 6, 7, 8, 2026. Rehearsals will
be in January - March 2026. Actors are paid an honourarium and get free parking.

If you would like to audition, please send your headshot and resume to
janet@peninsulaproductions.org 

We look forward to hearing from you!

 #peninsulaproductions #arts #culture #theatre #stage #supporthearts #surreybc #auditions #actors

items.text:
Hello, my name is David. I‚Äôm local to the Norwalk / Los Angeles area and wanted to introduce myself to the group.

I‚Äôm a filmmaker and content creator, and I recently started renting out my camera gear to help new and aspiring filmmakers who may not be ready to buy their own equipment yet or just need gear for a specific project.

I currently have a Sony a7 V production kit available. I‚Äôm happy to work with beginners, answer setup questions, and make the process easy and low pressure. Everything is booked and insured through ShareGrid for safety on both sides.

If anyone here needs a camera for an upcoming shoot, or just wants to take a look, here‚Äôs the link:
https://www.sharegrid.com/losangeles/l/426639-complete-sony-a7-v-production-kit?utm_medium=social&utm_source=clipboard&utm_term=complete_sony_a7_v_production_kit

Feel free to comment or message me if you have questions. Looking forward to connecting with everyone here.

items.text: Aspiring filmmakers...My workbook is LIVE! I have been asked over and over and hosted seminars at the National Black Theatre Festival to share - - - how I was able to get 2 movies on TubiTv and Prime Video in less than 2 years - yes I have receipts, screenshots in the book p. 87 - when the industry says it should have taken 2 years to get 1 movie live. That is because I am part of the God reset program...hee, hee...I mentioned that on a video. I am grateful to God. In this book I am sharing step by step how I did got my two movies streaming on the best networks. The workbook has space in the book for you to do your work and track your process! Now is your time to go from dreaming to streaming! Buy your copy of "How to Go From Dreaming to Streaming" today on Amazon.com (Amazon is working on merging my products.) Love you guys! Be blessed. [https://business.amazon.com/abredir/author/ednathompson]

This regional conference brings together NATS teachers and students from Arizona, California, Hawai‚Äòi, Nevada, and Utah, and I‚Äôm honored to be participating as:
üé§ A workshop presenter
üéº A judge
üåü A proud teacher with two students advancing to the semifinals

üé∂ About the BeSingGargle¬© Workshop

BeSingGargle¬© is a playful, water-based vocal warm-up designed to help singers:

 ‚Ä¢ Open range and smooth register transitions
 ‚Ä¢ Breathe with more ease and clarity
 ‚Ä¢ Shape vowels and consonants with greater freedom
 ‚Ä¢ Quickly and naturally clear phlegm while lightly lubricating the voice
 ‚Ä¢ Calm nerves and boost confidence through gentle vagal and sensory activation

A special bonus: BeSingGargle¬© works beautifully online, making it a powerful and engaging tool for virtual voice lessons as well as in-person teaching.

The session will include a live demonstration, a student demo, and hands-on participation. It‚Äôs joyful, grounding, and surprisingly effective, helping singers move out of their heads, into their bodies, and onto the stage with confidence and ease.

*CALL FOR CROWD PARTICIPANTS (EXTRAS) // UNPAID*

*Berlin, SO36, 04.01.2026*

For our student short film project _Signal One_ we are looking for people to be part of the *background crowd* in a punk club scene, shot at *SO36 Berlin* around noon on *January 4th, 2026* .

What the movie is about: _After meeting face-to-face with the punk scene in 1977s West Berlin, a Yugoslav philosophy student has to learn how to confront and accept the person he really is._

We are looking for around 50 people who want to go wild in a *70s punk club scene* and are happy to dress accordingly. All ages and all genders welcome!

Unfortunately, the project is unpaid but we will provide snacks on set. Estimated shooting time: *approx. 3-4 hours* , starting around noon.

If you‚Äôre interested or want more information, feel free to text me by phone or send an email to signalone.casting@posteo.de. 

Looking forward to hearing from you :)

---

Worum es im Film geht:

_Nachdem er der Punk-Szene im West-Berlin von 1977 begegnet ist, muss ein jugoslawischer Philosophiestudent lernen, sich seiner eigenen Identit√§t zu stellen und diese zu akzeptieren._

Wir suchen ca. 50 Personen, die Lust haben, in einer *70er-Punkclub-Szene* die Partyg√§ste zu spielen und sich passend zu kleiden. Alle Altersgruppen und Geschlechter willkommen!

Das Projekt ist unbezahlt, aber es wird Snacks am Set geben.

Gesch√§tzte Drehzeit: *ca. 3‚Äì4 Stunden* , ab Mittag.

Wenn du interessiert bist oder mehr Informationen haben m√∂chtest, melde dich gern direkt unter dieser Nummer oder E-Mail an signalone.casting@posteo.de

Wir freuen uns auf eure Nachrichten! :)

Hi all, happy New Year! I hope this is okay to post here...I am a local actor and recent USC grad looking to update my reel footage, and I wanted to see if there are any other actors out there who would be interested in filming a scene together to use for your reel as well?

I've produced a handful of short films and web series in the past and will happily write a scene based on your character type and provide you with raw and edited footage. I'm hoping to film in the South Denver/Littleton/Centennial area in mid-January (but flexible!) Let me know if you're interested; the best way to get in touch is via email to aspenksomers@gmail.com. TIA!

items.text:
This is a question for all sag union people out there. Originally our feature film untethered we wanted make a sag film but after talking to my EP he recommended that we book a sag E actress and currently we are talking to on.

My question is under sag aftra rules what are the requirements for sag Eligible contracts, when it comes down to payment and per day?

topComments.text: Tyler Schacht in other words, if you hire a sag eligible actor, there are no contract rules for you to abide by. Only if they are Sag members already. Sag eligible means the actor has enough taft Hartley credits to apply to sag but have not applied yet...they are still nonunion. Whomever you hire, you can check to see if thry are sag or nonunion simply by calling the sag office and checking them thoroughly. The office can tell you, the casting director, if they are registered sag members or not.

Hi Tyler. SAG-AFTRA Actor and signatory producer here. You‚Äôre getting some incomplete answers. Basically it comes down to whether or not you decided to make your project under a SAG-AFTRA contract or not.  And pay requirements depend on the type of SAG-AFTRA contract you decided to use for your project. It has nothing to do with the union eligibility of one of the actors. 

Most of the people on this thread are correct about the SAG eligible Actor. SAG eligible means they are still non-union. They are eligible to join the union, but have not yet done so. So if your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA contract, they are still allowed to work your project, and there are no considerations you have to worry about in regard to the union. However, no SAG-AFTRA MEMBER actors may work on your nonunion project. 

This is where a lot of your answers are incomplete. If you did your project in a SAG-AFTRA contract, depending on the type of contract, you may or may not have to pay your actors at all. Even if they are SAG-AFTRA members. However, doing your project under a SAG contract will allow SAG-AFTRA members to act in your project. Contracts like SAG micro budget, SAG student, SAG Indie, and SAG ultra low budget all have ways of allowing for ultra low budget projects to do things like defer pay or no pay for actors. Even if they are full members of the union. But if you make your project a SAG-AFTRA contract project, then ALL actors in the project are covered and protected by SAG-AFTRA rules. This means that if you had budgeted a pay rate for actors, then all actors whether they are union members or not, would be subject to the same pay scale. Whether that is no pay, $150 a day, or $1000 a day. SAG-AFTRA contracts are not about treating some actors better than others. They are about making sure that all actors are protected, treated fairly, and paid fairly and most important transparently.

So if I am understanding correctly, you have a non-union project, that has employed a SAG-AFTRA eligible Actor. In this case, you have absolutely no requirements regarding the union. This is because your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA agreement.  the rules are about your project status. Not about the Actor‚Äôs eligibility status.
